# Part II — Long-Term Product Vision

---

### 9. Vision

Project Sarthi should become the understanding layer for software engineering.

Current development tools excel at writing code.

Git stores history.

VS Code edits files.

GitHub stores repositories.

Postman tests APIs.

Database clients manage data.

Each tool understands one aspect of software.

Project Sarthi understands the relationships between them.

Its purpose is not to replace existing tools.

Its purpose is to connect them through understanding.

---

### 10. The Long-Term Goal

Imagine a developer opening a large unfamiliar repository.

Instead of spending several days exploring folders, they connect it to Project Sarthi.

Within minutes they understand:

Project architecture.

Major modules.

Dependencies.

Request flow.

Database relationships.

Documentation quality.

Potential risks.

Current project health.

Recent evolution.

